From Simon Tardell Subject Re Sunrise sunset times In Joseph Wetstein writes I am looking for a program or algorithm that can be used to compute sunrise and sunset I would appreciate any I once thought it would be easiest fitting a sine to the But This gave discrepancy of upto six If you fit a sine series you'll get a very good fit after just three or four terms This presumably has to do with the eccentricity of the Earths Simon Tardell V ga v gra cgs